For `eww', I think you need to treat the 402 result like a 200 result:

{{{
(let ((fake-line '(402 OK "Payment required but we don't care")))
  ;; sadly, url-http-codes is a defconst, so we cannot use let to bind it
  (condition-case err
      (progn
       (setq url-http-codes (cons fake-line url-http-codes))
       (eww "https://www.emacswiki.org/"))
    (t (setq url-http-codes (delete fake-line url-http-codes)))))
}}}

On my system, it still doesn't work because I meddle with cookies and `url-privacy-level' so it fails somewhere else.
It works with ##emacs -Q##, however.
